Using Sphinx 1.0b2, for the mapserver.org documentation, when trying to use the latex builder to generate PDF output, with a &#x27;make all-pdf&#x27; command, the following restructured text:

{{{\\
GAP [int]\\
.. deprecated:: 6.0

{code}
     This keyword has been deprecated in version 6.0. It has been replaced by the same keyword in the :ref:`STYLE`.
{code}

}}}

..causes the following error when trying to &#x27;make all-pdf&#x27;:

{{{\\
! Undefined control sequence.\\
l.8079 ...m[{GAP {[}int{]}}] \leavevmodeDeprecated\\
since version 6.0.\\
}}}

..but the following restructured text works fine:

{{{\\
GAP [int]\\
This keyword has been deprecated in version 6.0. It has been replaced by the same keyword in the :ref:{{STYLE}}.

{code}
     .. deprecated:: 6.0
{code}

}}}

Is this a Sphinx issue?

-jeff

